 <div class="title" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Appendix 1: After the Climate Shift</div>
 <p id="Par65" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">First note that the optimal choice of fossil fuel 
  <span class="italic">E</span> and renewable energy 
  <span class="italic">R</span> is made at each point in time, without affecting the dynamics of the problem. Therefore, we can simplify the problem by defining the maximum level of output 
  <span class="italic">Y net</span> of input costs and capital depreciation:
  <div id="Equ17" class="disp-formula">
   <span class="label">A1</span>
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M95" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$ Y(K,\pi ) \equiv \mathop {\text{Max}}\limits_{E,R} \;\left[ {(1 - \pi )AF(K,E,R) - dE - cR - \delta K} \right]. $$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M96" display="block" class="math">
     <div class="mrow">
      <span class="mi">Y</span>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span stretchy="false" class="mo">(</span>
       <span class="mi">K</span>
       <span class="mo">,</span>
       <span class="mi">π</span>
       <span stretchy="false" class="mo">)</span>
      </div>
      <span class="mo">≡</span>
      <div class="munder">
       <span class="mtext">Max</span>
       <div class="mrow">
        <span class="mi">E</span>
        <span class="mo">,</span>
        <span class="mi">R</span>
       </div>
      </div>
      <span width="0.277778em" class="mspace"/>
      <div close="]" open="[" class="mfenced">
       <div class="mrow">
        <span stretchy="false" class="mo">(</span>
        <span class="mn">1</span>
        <span class="mo">-</span>
        <span class="mi">π</span>
        <span stretchy="false" class="mo">)</span>
        <span class="mi">A</span>
        <span class="mi">F</span>
        <span stretchy="false" class="mo">(</span>
        <span class="mi">K</span>
        <span class="mo">,</span>
        <span class="mi">E</span>
        <span class="mo">,</span>
        <span class="mi">R</span>
        <span stretchy="false" class="mo">)</span>
        <span class="mo">-</span>
        <span class="mi">d</span>
        <span class="mi">E</span>
        <span class="mo">-</span>
        <span class="mi">c</span>
        <span class="mi">R</span>
        <span class="mo">-</span>
        <span class="mi">δ</span>
        <span class="mi">K</span>
       </div>
      </div>
