  </div>
 </p>
 <p id="Par68" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Optimality requires 
  <div id="IEq43" class="inline-formula">
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M107" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$ U'(C^{A} ) = V_{K}^{A} (K,\pi ), $$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M108" class="math">
     <div class="mrow">
      <div class="msup">
       <span class="mi">U</span>
       <span class="mo">′</span>
      </div>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span stretchy="false" class="mo">(</span>
