    <span xlink:href="10640_2018_231_Article_IEq44.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div>
 </p>
 <p id="Par69" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Differentiating (
  <a rid="Equ18" ref-type="" href="#Equ18">A2</a>) with respect to 
  <span class="italic">K</span>, using this optimality condition and a 
  <span class="italic">CRRA</span> utility function 
  <span class="italic">U</span>, yields a differential equation for consumption after the regime shift 
  <span class="italic">C</span>
  <span class="sup">
   <span class="italic">A</span>
  </span> as a function of 
  <span class="italic">K</span>:
  <div id="Equ19" class="disp-formula">
   <span class="label">A3</span>
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M111" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$ \left[ {Y(K,\pi ) - C^{A} (K,\pi )} \right]C_{K}^{A} (K,\pi ) = \sigma \left[ {Y_{K} (K,\pi ) - \rho } \right]C^{A} (K,\pi ), $$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M112" display="block" class="math">
